# Root .dockerignore — applies to every `docker build` invoked from
# the repository root. Keeps the build context small (sub-200 MB) so
# buildx layer caching is fast.
#
# We INTENTIONALLY allow `apps/`, `packages/`, `services/`, `configs/`,
# `templates/`, and the workspace manifests — the dashboard Dockerfile
# needs them all in the `deps` stage. We exclude only artefacts the
# multi-stage build will regenerate, plus repo metadata.

# Build artefacts — regenerated by multi-stage builds.
**/node_modules
**/.next
**/.turbo
**/dist
**/build
**/coverage
**/out
**/*.tsbuildinfo

# Test artefacts.
**/playwright-report
**/test-results
**/__visual_baselines__
**/.nyc_output

# Editor / VCS / OS metadata.
.git
.gitignore
.gitattributes
.github
.vscode
.idea
**/.DS_Store
**/Thumbs.db
**/*.swp
**/*.iml

# Env files — secrets enter via Kubernetes Secret + Infisical at runtime.
**/.env
**/.env.local
**/.env.*.local

# Foreign lockfiles — workspace is pnpm-only.
**/package-lock.json
**/yarn.lock

# Local-only spawner worktrees.
.spawn-worktrees/

# Cache trees.
.pnpm-store/
.caia/
